1
00:00:00,150 --> 00:00:01,810
Hi and welcome back.

2
00:00:01,890 --> 00:00:06,290
In this lesson we'll show you how to add text in formulas.

3
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:12,570
It's an important trick that will be very helpful a bit later in the course whenever you start creating

4
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:17,230
a function and you add this type of quotation mark to it.

5
00:00:17,310 --> 00:00:23,680
Excel knows that what is included within the quotation marks should be read as text.

6
00:00:23,730 --> 00:00:26,620
For example I'll type equal.

7
00:00:26,790 --> 00:00:34,420
And then within quotation marks revenue let's press enter and see what happens.

8
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:40,260
Excel displays revenue as text perfect if that's clear.

9
00:00:40,260 --> 00:00:42,520
Let's try something a bit different now.

10
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:53,830
I'll add a blank space in front of revenue within the function and as you see this has affected our

11
00:00:53,830 --> 00:00:54,760
output.

12
00:00:54,760 --> 00:01:02,170
The text revenue starts one character space to the right and we have a blank space in front of it.

13
00:01:02,170 --> 00:01:08,430
This means that blank spaces are important especially in certain situations.

14
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:18,750
Okay great let's provide another useful example in these two columns we have data that should be united.

15
00:01:19,030 --> 00:01:22,180
We have a country's name and its capital.

16
00:01:22,180 --> 00:01:32,730
Let's put them together I can do that in the following way sell a 5 and sell B 5 press enter and here's

17
00:01:32,730 --> 00:01:34,590
the output we obtained.

18
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:37,710
Doesn't look very good does it.

19
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:39,720
Most definitely not.

20
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:47,270
So to separate them I'll add a third arguments united to both cells with another Ampersand function.

21
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:52,840
It will only contain a comma with inverted brackets okay.

22
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,810
Very well.

23
00:01:53,890 --> 00:01:58,280
Let's PRESENTER Now the situation has improved a little.

24
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:04,720
There is some separation between a country's name and its capital but we need to add a blank space in

25
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:08,430
front of the capital city to make this a bit better.

26
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:15,280
I'll add a third Ampersand sign and we'll simply include a blank space within brackets.

27
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:19,930
This creates my blank space in front of each capital city.

28
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,430
I believe this is what we were after.

29
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:26,770
So this is how we work with text in Excel.

30
00:02:26,770 --> 00:02:33,160
A bit later in the course you will learn why this is very useful when creating dynamic functions but

31
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,040
you don't have to worry about that now.

32
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:38,910
You are making excellent progress already so enjoy that.
